ます.description: (ます) - used to indicate respect for the listener (or reader); used to indicate respect for those affected by the action

ま.description: (ま) - (when urging or consoling) just (e.g. "just wait here")/come now/now, now; tolerably/passably/moderately/reasonably/fairly/rather/somewhat; (when hesitating to express an opinion) well.../I think.../it would seem.../you might say.../Hmmm, I guess so...; oh!/oh dear!/oh, my!/wow!/goodness gracious!/good heavens!

し.description: (し) - (at the end of a phrase) notes one (of several) reasons

て.description: (て) - (で after certain verb forms)  indicates continuing action

な.description: (な) - (sentence end, mainly masc.) indicates emotion or emphasis; (from なさい) (used with masu stem verb) command; (used with dictionary form verb) prohibition

ど.description: (ド) - (occ. written 度 ) precisely/exactly/plumb/totally/very much; damn/stupid/cursed

こ.description: (っこ) - doing/in such a state; doing together/contest/match; familiarizing suffix (sometimes meaning "small")
